body.name: Fit + Fresh Metro Tote 2-in-1 Quilted Multi-Purpose Travel Bag
features: DUAL-COMPARTMENT: The work tote bag for women measures at 18"x6”x14" to hold all office essentials. One compartment fits a 15" laptop, folders, books, and more. While the second insulated section of the large tote bag for women holds food and drinks.

THERMAL INSULATION: This large tote bag women love can simplify your life with its’ 2-in-1 functions! The insulated cooler portion is lined with BPA-free PEVA material, 5mm thick padding, and 300D polyester to keep food and drinks fresh for hours.

VERSATILE FOR ON-THE-GO: Don’t juggle multiple bags with this all-in-one tote! Whether you're heading to the office, or a work trip, this is the perfect large tote bag for women for work, laptop tote bag for women, tote bag for women.

EASY TO CLEAN: Cooler compartment interior of this large laptop tote bag for women easily wipes clean. Features heat-welded seams to guard against potential leaks. The high quality flexible, quilted nylon exterior clean easily too with soapy water!

FIT & FRESH: Based in Providence, RI, Fit + Fresh prides itself on creating functional and distinctive styles for women and men. Our stylish, reusable insulated lunch bags have lasting durability, for anyone on-the-go!
body.description: Are you tired of juggling your laptop bag, purse and lunch bag? Here’s your solution- the Quilted Tote! This spacious tote features two zippered compartments- one insulated and one non-insulated. The insulated compartment features leakproof, easy to clean lining and is perfect for packing your lunch, snacks and a drink or two for the day. The non-insulated compartment is great for work accessories such as a laptop, notebook and files and features an interior zippered pocket for pens, pencils and your flash drive. This lightweight tote comes in neutral colors that are perfect for your work or office environment while still showing off your style- whether you work in a classroom, a cubicle or a corner office!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid everyday bag
reviews.reviewText: So in love with this bag. The construction is solid, color is beautiful and oh so practical. Everyone that sees it want one. Its comfortable to carry and even fits my 70oz water bottle and lunch on the lined side, with iPad and files on the other side. Just get it. You wont regret it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This bag is just the right size to hold my laptop, some papers, personal items, and my lunch. I love only carrying one bag to work! If I could’ve given 4 1/2 stars I would have. The lunch compartment doesn’t keep things as cold as I’d like. If you add a big ice pack it helps, but then you’re adding even more weight. However, for the convenience of carrying only one bag I’ll deal with it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and functional
reviews.reviewText: I like that there isn’t a cheesy brand label on this like so many bags do. The color is nice (I got the purple), it’s spacious, and has comfortable handles. I carry this bag to work and like being able to separate my lunch in the waterproof slightly insulated side. I can put my heels and other things in the other pocket. Plenty big for a laptop as well. I don’t carry a ton since I walk a lot and I don’t want it to get too heavy, but I could definitely fit a lot in the bag if I needed to. I can see taking this on road trips too for the insulated side.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love! Just wish it had a shoulder strap optio
reviews.reviewText: I love that I can keep food items separately in one bag! Both sides are pretty roomy, I can fit quite a few things inside. The only thing I feel like is missing is an option for a shoulder strap. I’m a mom so a lot of the times I have to carry multiple things, including my toddler sometimes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I needed a bag for work to carry my laptop & lunch, etc. I wasn’t sure about this from the pics but it’s actually very nice looking. It has held up well after using it for almost a year. I would buy this bag again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had this for probably a year or more and I’m not easy with it, I use it. I love it!! It’s perfect for my everyday purse to work and then the side I can pack my lunch and snacks. Easy to clean. Absolutely durable. No problems. Thinking about buying another color!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this bag for work and I absolutely love it. It has large pockets and sections. The insulated side is a major plus! You really could use this bag for anything. The only downside is the fabric slightly fades after use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Fell apart after a few months....
reviews.reviewText: The handle tore apart a few months after purchase (within 3-6mths). The inside section for the lunch boxes came undone also (sewing came apart). I ended up stitching the handles back together and it works. I still get compliments on the bag due to the leopard pattern, but not the greatest with durability. Eventually I will have to find something else...

Ok this is a first impression review because I haven’t actually used it yet, just put all my things in. But it has two awesome big pockets. I have a 2L water bottle I tote around with me, plus lots of food with glass storage containers. They all fit. Plus the other pocket for my laptop and etc. and then there is also a small inner pocket and a pocket on the outside. So far I am in love but I will update if that changes
This lunch/lined bag is perfect for carrying lunch on one side and the other side is great for my wallet, phone and essential items I take to work daily

Busqué mucho tiempo una lonchera con el suficiente espacio y esta tiene la ventaja de que puedes utilizarla como bolsa, es ideal para profesores o personas que trabajan fuera gran parte del día y necesitan llevar varias comidas.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good laptop/lunch tote. Wish there were smaller sizes.
reviews.reviewText: The only tote I could find with only a section for a laptop and insulated section for you lunch. Most other totes try to be your purse as well, but I love my purses and hated having to get everything out of my laptop bag to put in my purse when I don’t want to take my laptop bag around on errands like grocery shopping or going for dinner.There’s a separate zipper for each compartment (lunch and laptop). There’s a small inside zippered pocket for the power cord. There’s a small outside zippered pocket where I put earbuds and phone charger. Well priced.My only complaints are that it doesn’t come in smaller sizes. Most laptops are 13” nowadays. This one can fit a 17” laptop. It could also be a little more stylish. Anyway, maybe it’s meant more to be a giant beach bag, because that’s what it looks like when I’m carrying it to work. But it’s not an eyesore.
